The extract is then diluted to the optimal concentration in medium-chain triglyceride (MCT) oil and encapsulated in an easy-to-swallow softgel. Effects may take longer than dried flower to kick in but are longer-lasting, up to 12 hours or longer. Each bottle contains 30 gel capsules containing 9 - 12 mg of CBD each. Remember to start slowly with a low dose.

Grown in a sunlight-filled, high-tech greenhouse in British Columbia, the buds are trimmed and hand-groomed, dried and cured with care. Each Balance 1:1 pack contains the strain Pennywise, a legacy cut known for its balanced cannabinoids, with smooth aromas ranging from earthy to herbal.

Products.Name: Pure Sunfarms Corp - D. Bubba

LongDescription.en: Born in California but raised in BC, Pure Sunfarms' Headband is a hybrid of OG Kush and Sour Diesel that became popular in Ontario before finding a home in BC's temperate climate. The dense, elegantly contoured flowers exhibit a range of green colours under a coat of sticky trichomes. It offers savoury flavours of allspice and nutmeg (caryophyllene), lavender (linalool), lemon and coriander seeds (humulene). The combination of these terpenes results in its signature 'gassy' smell.

LongDescription.en: Pure Sunfarms' cut of Pink Kush from BC's Vancouver Island is a coastal relative of the legendary OG Kush. This special strain is beloved across Canada for its strong aromas, colourful flowers and high THC potential. Beneath a thick coating of trichomes, the dense and round buds feature forest green leaves, often with a purple hue, mixed with dark amber pistils. Grown in a high-tech greenhouse in the Fraser Valley, each bud is carefully trimmed and hand-groomed, dried and cured to precise standards. Pink Kush showcases gassy aromas of white pepper, orange, butterscotch, coffee, earth and grapefruit, the result of a rich combination of terpenes that includes caryophyllene, myrcene, humulene, bisabolol, and limonene.

Products.Name: Pure Sunfarms Corp - Balance

ShortDescription.en: Pure Sun CBD 14 g Dried Flower

LongDescription.en: Pure Sunfarms Pure Sun CBD is a hand-selected phenotype of the Cannatonic strain. Grown in a high-tech greenhouse in BC's Fraser Valley, each bud is carefully trimmed and hand groomed, dried and cured to precise standards. The dried flowers are tight and compact, featuring a mix of pale and jade green leaves dotted with a generous dusting of trichomes. The delicate aromas and flavours are reminiscent of fresh flowers (bisabolol), creamsicle and brown sugar (myrcene) and cardamom (guaiol).

Instructions.en: Inhalation, vaporization, or baked into homemade edibles.

Products.Name: Pure Sunfarms Corp - Pure Sun CBD

LongDescription.en: White Rhino is a classic B.C. bud strain, developed on the west coast before it became popular across Canada. It's an indica-dominant hybrid of White Widow and proprietary strains from Brazil and India, grown in a high-tech greenhouse in British Columbia. Nearly hidden beneath a cover of snowy trichomes, the leaves of this compact bud showcase a variety of colours, ranging from sea green to lime peel, with splashes of amethyst. Our phenotype was specifically selected for its fruity aromas of blueberries and mangos (myrcene), green grapes (pinene) and Thai basil (caryophyllene).

Instructions.en: Inhalation, vaporization, or baked into homemade edibles.

LongDescription.en: Indiva developed Artisan Batch as a way to give local growers the chance for national exposure. As part of this program, Artisan Batch is proud to launch Coast Mountain Cannabis BC Original Glue. BC Original Glue (GG4) is an indica-dominant hybrid strain, grown by Coast Mountain Cannabis in the pristine Pemberton Valley, just north of Whistler in the heart of British Columbia's mountains.  The award-winning Original Glue strain was first developed by GG Strains as a hybrid, combining Chem's Sister, Sour Dubb and Chocolate Diesel. It's become known for its pungent earthy and sour aromas and medium-density buds. Harvested Coast Mountain Cannabis plants are dried using the cold cure method to preserve the terpenes and enhance the overall quality and flavour. And, thanks to small batch production, they're hand-trimmed to produce an ultra-premium finished product. LongDescription.en: Pink Lemonade - This strain smells fruity, and screams lemons and grapefruit on the exhale. The bud is coated in a generous layer of trichomes atop jade foliage and bronze pistils. With a higher difficulty to grow, you can be rewarded with very high THC percentages and incredible terpene profiles. This genetic prefers warmer climates, so cold nights are to be avoided and should be harvested before October in North America.  Seeds are feminized.

Products.Name: Atlas Growers Ltd. - Pink Lemonade

LongDescription.en: Power Kush -- Combining a Dutch classic, with another worldwide staple strain creates this beautiful hybrid cultivar with impressive THC delivery, and yields out of this world. This is an indoor dominant plant, but can still be grown outdoors with some attention and care taken toward the end of the grow cycle. This cultivar prefers warmer climates, and does have a fairly large stretch rate during early flower. Large, dense flower sites, and very pungent aroma make this a treat to grow and enjoy! This medium-yield plant generally offers between 18 and 24 per cent THC and less than one per cent CBD. The OG Kush and Power Plant cross flowers at between 8.5 and 9 weeks.

Products.Name: Atlas Growers Ltd. - Power Kush

LongDescription.en: Bubba Kush 2.5 -- Bubba Kush is an indica-heavy and high-THC producing genetic. This plant will produce dark green flowers with purple pigments in late flower, with an incredibly pungent and classic aroma and flavour. The higher stretch rate will complement the larger yields, but should considered when growing either indoors or outdoors. Bubba Kush is a beginner-friendly cultivar and is resistant to mould and pests, which makes it a great candidate for all growing types. Colder temperatures and environments should be avoided. This high-yield plant offers between 18 and 28 per cent THC and less than one per cent CBD. The Bubba Kush 2.0 and  Bubba Kush #1 cross flowers between 8 and 8.5 weeks.

Products.Name: Atlas Growers Ltd. - Bubba Kush 2.5

LongDescription.en: Triple Scoop-- Triple Scoop has a flower time of 8 to 9 weeks, higher stretch rate and incredible flower structure. This strain is suited for indoor growing as it requires warmer temperatures and more control with humidity. With high considerations for trellising, or training, heights should be monitored. Yield will not be sacrificed for the quality that will be produced, and it's considered a beginner-friendly strain to grow! Offering between 17 and 27 per cent THC and less than one per cent CBD, Triple Scoop is a cross of Sorbet, Grape L.A. and OG.

LongDescription.en: Winner of Grow Opportunity Magazine's 2020 Canada's Grower of the Year. Reef's High Seas owes its high-THC potency to its award-winning lineage. High Seas is the name we've given to our batches of Ghost Train Haze with particularly high percentages of THC. Ghost Train Haze, a sativa-dominant strain born from a cross between Ghost OG and Nevil's Wreck, produces dense buds that are laden with resinous, crystal trichomes. With a terpene profile that includes terpinolene, myrcene, limonene and beta-pinene, High Seas' aroma is fresh and earthy, and its flavour is citrusy. The plant is grown either aquaponically or in living soil with no synthetic fertilizers or pesticides.

Instructions.en: Start low and go slow.  Vapourization or combustion recommended.

LongDescription.en: Coastal Kush is an indica-dominant variety that crosses the powerful MK Ultra and fellow Colorado native Chemdawg 91 - known as Cold Creek Kush. This variety has enjoyed a second-place finish at the High Times Cannabis Cup in the indica category. Reef Organic's Coastal Kush has a unique terpene profile that produces a sweet and herbaceous aroma with subtle notes of floral and spice. This organically grown Kush has a fresh taste and balanced effects. Reef Organi's cannabis is grown organically in living soil in small indoor batches, free of synthetic fertilizers or pesticides. It is dried and cured in small batches for perfect moisture levels, high consistency, potency and that desired white ash and clean burn. Coastal Kush is sensory tested, hand-finished, weighed and inspected before release to consumers.

Instructions.en: For inhalation. When smoking/vapourizing, wait a few minutes between inhalations to gauge effects.

LongDescription.en: Affirma Soft Chews are made with full-spectrum extract, which provides not only the tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) but also various other minor cannabinoids, terpenes, flavonoids and other substances present in the cannabis plant. These plant compounds are responsible for the cannabis taste and flavour of the extract. The effect of the combination of these compounds, acting together with the THC, has been described as the 'entourage effect', which has been shown to enhance many of the potentially beneficial characteristics of THC. Affirma's 1-pack contains a total of 10mg of THC. Each gummy contains 10mg of THC.

Instructions.en: Ready to eat product. If you are a new user of cannabis it is recommended to consume a quarter to a half of a unit to start.

LongDescription.en: King T is all kinds of suave and cool. This sativa-dominant strain, also known as Tutankhamon, has powers only a true ruler could possess and knows exactly how he wants his kingdom to react to him. Of course, his name pays homage to one of Egypt's most mighty Pharaohs, and his strain is just as mighty as the name. As a descendent of AK-47, he is extremely rare and works to create a cerebral effect in all those who come across his power of a near 20 per cent THC level. King T wants a world where everyone feels good and gets along, and because of this, he's ideal to bring out for your daytime activities, exercise or social events. What might a King smell like? Why, only the finest citrus and earthy aroma and flavour profile with a sour, skunky touch. Tutankhamon gains this aroma through his 60-day flowering cycle where he produces an abundant amount of cottony, crystal-coated buds with lots of trichomes.

Instructions.en: When smoking or using a vaporizer, wait for a few minutes between inhalations to gauge the strength of the effects. Remember to start low and go slow.

Products.Name: 314 Pure Cannabis Ltd. - King T

LongDescription.en: It's time to vibe out at the pool with our main man Chem Dawg. Why the name Chem Dawg? Well, he has a bit of an uncertain past with no-one truly knowing his genetic history, but who doesn't love a bit of a mystery man? While there are many origin stories regarding this hunk, everyone is able to agree on his abilities. With a THC level between 15 and 20 per cent, flowering within 9 to 10 weeks, and coming in at over a whopping five feet tall, Chem Dawg is no-one to mess around with. He rolls up with a diesel fuel aroma, sour inhale and ammonia-like taste on the exhale. You won't be able to miss him with his loose leaves, sticky white trichomes and long, tapered buds. As a close knit crew, his buds are pretty hard to break up, so a grinder is definitely recommended. Grab yourself a 3.5g flower pouch if you and your buds want to keep the conversation flowing.

Instructions.en: When smoking or using a vaporizer, wait for a few minutes between inhalations to gauge the strength of the effects. Remember to start low and go slow.

Products.Name: 314 Pure Cannabis Ltd. - Chem Dawg

LongDescription.en: Ladies look out, here comes Poolboy Bruce. This powerful strain is made from dense buds resulting in a THC content that reaches nearly 25%. Bruce believes life is all about balance and that's why he's here to bring you the perfect combination of Sativa and Indica effects. Fun facts about Bruce he tastes of a pungent citrus but compared to his smell, tastes a little earthier (loves gardening) and less sweet (not too big of a sweet tooth on this guy). Now I know you're all thinking Wow Bruce sounds amazing. Where in the world did he come from? Well, bred by Jason Holck of Dark Horse Genetics, he was cross bred with Strawberry Diesel and OG Kush. Similar to other plants of this strain, it took Bruce 8 to 10 weeks to reach his full potential and let me tell you, he was a sight to behold. Rich magenta hued leaves, bright green buds frosted with large headed trichomes and red hairs. One look and you're thinking Damn, that dude is rad.

Instructions.en: When smoking or using a vaporizer, wait for a few minutes between inhalations to gauge the strength of the effects. Remember to start low and go slow.

LongDescription.en: When ICE and Cambodian Landrace were cross bred by growers at Nirvana Seeds they created a sativa dominant hybrid that was ready to take on it's job of elevating moods. It packs a punch while still maintaining a smooth high that both medicinal and recreational users will enjoy.  Raspberry Cough is definitely a morning guy, so a smoke right as the alarm goes off or as a midday pick me up, will set you on the right track for a productive day. This little ball of sunshine brings on an instant cerebral high perfect for mental clarity. Whether you need motivation for a busy day of errands or focus for a daunting day at work, he's here to help. And when you need to be productive, there's no time for stress. As if he couldn't get any better, Raspberry Cough is a tasty little bugger with a touch of spice to his flavour profile and leaving a nice raspberry aftertaste. The sweet berry also comes out with his scent accompanied by an earthy nuttiness. He can be known to make you cough (hence the last name) but that's hardly a downfall compared to the warm sensation that will run through your body leaving you relaxed yet functional.

Instructions.en: When smoking or using a vaporizer, wait for a few minutes between inhalations to gauge the strength of the effects. Remember to start low and go slow.

ShortDescription.en: Next Generation Critical Magic 4 Feminized Seeds

LongDescription.en: Bred by Next Generation Seeds from Alberta, this feminized hybrid between Critical Bilbo and Grapefruit haze is a pleasure to grow and smoke. It is aromatic and tasty. The plants are very branchy and are a clone-maker's dream. The buds are dense, round and easy to grow. Flowering between 50 and 55 days.

Instructions.en: Scuff outside of shell if possible using 80 grit sand paper. Put seeds in glass of distilled water for 24-48 hours Within 24-48 hours a tap root should be visible. Pour into a container with paper towel, drain water and allow root to develop 24 hrs. Transplant to desired medium.

Products.Name: Parkland Flower Inc. - Next Generation Critical Magic

ShortDescription.en: Next Generation Island Sweet Skunk 4 Feminized Seeds

LongDescription.en: Bred by Next Generation Seeds from Alberta, feminized Island Sweet Skunk is a classic. Perfect for the sea of green growers. Don't grow it with too many main tops indoors; it likes to grow as a single cola, but will branch a lot if topped. It's the ultimate in sweet sativas that produce big, with hints of fruit punch and grapefruit from this limonene-dominant variety. Flower time 65 to 70 days. It was the first-place winner of the BC Harvest Cup in British Columbia for two years straight.

Instructions.en: Scuff outside of shell if possible using 80 grit sand paper. Put seeds in glass of distilled water for 24-48 hours Within 24-48 hours a tap root should be visible. Pour into a container with paper towel, drain water and allow root to develop 24 hrs. Transplant to desired medium.

Products.Name: Parkland Flower Inc. - Next Generation Island Sweet Skunk

LongDescription.en: The fourth release of our M O U N T A I N series is an outdoor hybrid with an incredible aroma. We call this F6 high yielding, mold resistant strain K 4 I L A S H as homage to the crystal topped peak in Tibet. With THC levels, CBG, and CBC, this unique strain is sure to be a fan favourite. The terpene profile is composed of limonene, pinene, caryophyllene, myrcene and ocimene. Cultivated outside, this plant can become very large and requires around 63 days in flower to finish. The genetic heritage of K 4 I L A S H is Blueberry, Shoe Polish and Sour Diesel. Outdoor hybrid strain for the home grower. Mold resistant with tight buds a 9 week flowering period.

Products.Name: ProgenyBio Agricultural Services Inc. - K 4 I L A S H

LongDescription.en: E V E R E 5 T the fifth release of our M O U N T A I N series is an indoor indica dominant strain that is sure to be a classic. With genetic heritage from Mendocino Purps and OG Kush, this F3 cross has pedigree for greatness. The nose is a familiar cannabis skunk aroma as the terpene profile includes caryophyllene, myrcene, humulene and ocimene. This traditional indica dominant strain will yield large sticky flowers with high THC frosted peaks in 8 weeks of 12 hour light.

Products.Name: ProgenyBio Agricultural Services Inc. - E V E R E 5 T

LongDescription.en: Blue Gorilla derives its name from its strong genetics and sweet terpene profile. A vibrant cross between OG Kush, Gorilla Glue and Blueberry, this smooth, moderate-THC hybrid is densely stacked with frosted lime-green buds. It displays sweet scents of pine and fruit reminiscent of our natural, beautiful Muskoka home. Focused on delivering fresh product, Muskoka Grown packages its 3.5g using nitrogen injection to protect terpenes and cannabinoids.

Instructions.en: For inhalation. When smoking/vapourizing, wait a few minutes between inhalations to gauge effects.

Products.Name: Muskoka Grown Limited - Blue Gorilla

LongDescription.en: The Edge is a natural, earthy Sativa dominant hybrid cross between Northern Lights and Skunk #1. The forest-coloured, large buds are dusted in white trichomes and showcase flavours and aromas of pine, pickles, spice and citrus flavour. Reminding you of the good old days, this powerful variety has a skunk-appearance dotted with orange, and amber pistils. Focused on delivering fresh product, Muskoka Grown packages its 3.5g using nitrogen injection to protect terpenes and cannabinoids.

Instructions.en: For inhalation. When smoking/vapourizing, wait a few minutes between inhalations to gauge effects.

Products.Name: Muskoka Grown Limited - The Edge

LongDescription.en: Glueberry OG, fueled by some of today's best genetics, is a 3 way hybrid cross of GG #4, OG Kush and Blueberry. Grown indoors, this high THC hybrid features olive green flowers frosted with sugary amber trichomes and has a distinctive kush aroma with sweet and spicy taste notes. Focused on delivering fresh product, Muskoka Grown packages its 3.5g using nitrogen injection to protect terpenes and cannabinoids.

Instructions.en: For inhalation. When smoking/vapourizing, wait a few minutes between inhalations to gauge effects.

Products.Name: Muskoka Grown Limited - Glueberry OG

LongDescription.en: A potent cultivar with classic OG characteristics, Chem OG is a full-bodied, high-THC hybrid with everything you would expect in taste, aroma and terpene profile. Coming from a classic lineage of Chemdog 91's diesel fuel and San Fernando Valley OG earthy undertones, this powerful variety offers a strong gas aroma offset by subtle notes of citrus and herbs. The tightly-wound, smaller buds are frosted beneath a thick coat of silver trichomes, often with a purple hue, mixed with dusted orange pistils. Chem OG produces a strong, skunky perfume with undertones of rubber when burned. Focused on delivering fresh product, Muskoka Grown packages its 3.5g tins using nitrogen flushing to protect terpenes and cannabinoids.

Instructions.en: For inhalation. When smoking/vapourizing, wait a few minutes between inhalations to gauge effects.
